In a brief statement, the President addressed the ongoing auto strike and expressed his support for the United Auto Workers (UAW). He acknowledged the sacrifices made by auto workers and highlighted the need for fair compensation and benefits. The President emphasized the importance of unions in raising standards for workers and strengthening the overall economy. He called for a contract agreement that promotes good, middle-class jobs and supports the transition to a clean energy future. The President stated that while nobody wants a strike, he respects the workers' right to use collective bargaining options. He urged the parties to continue negotiations and dispatched two members of his team to offer support in reaching a contract agreement. The President concluded by emphasizing that auto workers deserve a contract that sustains them and the middle class.